Sec. 76.143. PUBLIC HEARING. As soon as practicable after
receiving a written request for a revision of a rule, an exemption
from a requirement of this chapter, or a prohibition of the spraying
of a regulated herbicide in an area, the department may hold a public
hearing to hear the request.
Added by Acts 1997, 75th Leg., ch. 1369, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1997.

